text: Piéla is a town in the Piéla Department of Gnagna Province in eastern Burkina Faso. The town has a population of 7710, and is the capital of the Piéla Department. ==References== ==External links== *Satellite map at Maplandia.com Category:Populated places in the Est Region (Burkina Faso) Category:Gnagna Province
title: Piéla
